 MARKETROID /mar'k@-troyd/ alt. MARKETING SLIME, MARKETING DROID, MARKETEER
n. Member of a company's marketing department, esp. one who promises users
that the next version of a product will have features which are unplanned,
extremely difficult to implement, and/or violate the laws of physics; and/or
one who describes existing features (and misfeatures) in ebullient,
buzzword-laden adspeak. Derogatory. Used by techies.